title: Provides that health insurance coverage may not deny reimbursements because the registered laboratory providing laboratory services has not been approved
summary: Provides that health insurance coverage may not deny reimbursements because the registered laboratory providing laboratory services has not been approved by the insurer or other entity; provides that in such case the insured pays excess costs therefor above the covered benefit.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the insurance law, in relation to health insurance coverage and eligibility for employee benefits provided by employee welfare funds for laboratory services
